&nbsp;
The state media published a photograph of Raisi's place in the Cabinet occupied by a photo of the president and a black turban, such as the one he used to wear. The Cabinet has not provided details on the time of the president's burial or succession plans.<br> The Iranian Foreign Minister, Hosein Amir Abdolahian, the governor of East Azerbaijan, Malik Rahmati, and the leader of Friday prayer in the city of Tabriz, Mohammad-Ali Al-Hashem, as well as an imprecise number of crew members. The cabinet was chaired by the first Iranian vice-president, Mohamad Mokhber, who according to the Iranian Constitution should take over the presidency.
